  <prompt>
    Conduct a comprehensive accessibility audit of the Office add-ins. Verify
    WCAG 2.1 AA compliance for all UI components, keyboard navigation, screen
    reader support, and high contrast mode.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Accessibility specialist. Expert in WCAG 2.1 guidelines and assistive
    technology testing.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Complete accessibility audit report documenting compliance status and any
    remediation items for WCAG 2.1 AA.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Office add-ins must be accessible to users with disabilities. Microsoft
      requires add-ins distributed via AppSource to meet WCAG 2.1 AA standards.
      This audit verifies compliance before production deployment.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/office-addins/shared/</file>
      <file>projects/sdap-office-integration/notes/</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec">MUST meet WCAG 2.1 AA standards</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">MUST support keyboard-only navigation</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">MUST work with common screen readers (NVDA, JAWS, Narrator)</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/sdap-office-integration/spec.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Prepare accessibility testing tools (axe, Accessibility Insights)</step>
    <step order="2">Run automated accessibility scan on all pages</step>
    <step order="3">Test keyboard navigation through save flow</step>
    <step order="4">Test keyboard navigation through share flow</step>
    <step order="5">Test with NVDA screen reader</step>
    <step order="6">Test with Windows Narrator</step>
    <step order="7">Test high contrast mode (all Windows themes)</step>
    <step order="8">Test focus management in dialogs</step>
    <step order="9">Verify ARIA labels and roles</step>
    <step order="10">Document all findings in audit report</step>
    <step order="11">Create remediation backlog for any issues</step>
    <step order="12">Update TASK-INDEX.md: change this task's status to âœ… completed</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="axe">Automated accessibility testing</tool>
    <tool name="accessibility-insights">Microsoft accessibility tool</tool>
    <tool name="nvda">Screen reader testing</tool>
    <tool name="narrator">Windows screen reader</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="docs">projects/sdap-office-integration/notes/accessibility-audit.md</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Automated scans report no critical issues</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All interactive elements keyboard accessible</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Screen reader announces all content correctly</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">High contrast mode is usable</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Audit report documents all findings</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Focus on the critical user journeys (save, share, quick create). Use
    Accessibility Insights for Windows for the most thorough testing.
    Document any known limitations with mitigation strategies.
  </notes>

